WEBVTT

00:01.918 --> 00:04.587
<i>[rock music]</i>

00:04.671 --> 00:06.089
<i>- ♪ Tear it down ♪</i>

00:06.172 --> 00:07.799
[laughter]

00:07.882 --> 00:11.136
- Hey, Caroline.

00:11.219 --> 00:13.722
Truth or dare?

00:13.805 --> 00:15.932
- Truth.
[all oohing]

00:16.015 --> 00:19.436
{\an9}- Have you ever given
road head?

00:19.519 --> 00:22.105
{\an8}- I'm not playing anymore.

00:22.188 --> 00:24.566
{\an8}- Totally a yes.

00:24.649 --> 00:27.569
{\an8}[laughter]

00:27.652 --> 00:29.070
{\an9}- My turn.

00:29.154 --> 00:32.448
{\an8}Mary Louise, truth or dare?
- Dare.

00:32.531 --> 00:34.200
{\an8}- I dare you

00:34.284 --> 00:36.578
{\an8}to stick this bottle
up your butt.

00:36.661 --> 00:39.664
{\an8}[laughter]

00:42.500 --> 00:45.295
{\an8}- Breathe deep!
- Start with the skinny side!

00:45.378 --> 00:47.422
{\an8}- Oh, right?
- Oh. Uh-uh.

00:47.505 --> 00:49.340
{\an8}- I hate when you guys do this.

00:49.424 --> 00:51.176
{\an8}You're acting
like a middle school clique.

00:51.259 --> 00:52.886
{\an8}- Oh, my God.
You're right.

00:52.969 --> 00:54.637
{\an8}That is so awesome.

00:54.721 --> 00:57.766
{\an8}[laughter]

01:01.060 --> 01:03.480
{\an8}[indistinct chatter]

01:03.563 --> 01:06.649
{\an9}- Kim Rigsby
and Claire Strauss.

01:06.733 --> 01:07.734
{\an8}John Glenn High School.

01:07.817 --> 01:09.986
{\an8}- Oh, Caroline Watson?

01:10.069 --> 01:12.947
{\an7}It's been years since someone's
called me by my maiden name.

01:13.031 --> 01:16.701
{\an8}- We're just a couple
old married ladies now.

01:16.785 --> 01:19.287
{\an9}- Wow.
Congratulations.

01:19.370 --> 01:20.997
{\an8}- So, what about you?

01:21.080 --> 01:22.499
{\an7}Did Jacob ever
put a ring on it?

01:22.582 --> 01:24.375
{\an9}- Oh, no.

01:24.459 --> 01:26.336
{\an8}We actually broke up.
- Yeah, I heard that.

01:26.419 --> 01:29.380
{\an8}- Then why did you ask?
- So, what have you been up to?

01:29.464 --> 01:32.550
{\an9}- I'm just single
and teaching.

01:32.634 --> 01:34.093
{\an8}- How brave.

01:34.177 --> 01:36.179
{\an7}- It is so great
to see you moving on.

01:36.262 --> 01:37.847
{\an8}- Jacob clearly has.

01:37.931 --> 01:40.642
{\an9}- Oh, no. He would've told me
if he was dating someone.

01:45.104 --> 01:47.398
{\an8}- I'm gonna need a ride
to the hospital.

01:47.482 --> 01:52.195
{\an8}♪ ♪

01:54.781 --> 01:57.700
{\an8}- Seriously, I'm fine.

02:00.370 --> 02:05.041
{\an8}[muffled wincing]

02:05.124 --> 02:06.918
{\an9}- Aren't you ashamed
of yourself?

02:07.001 --> 02:09.044
{\an8}You and your little group
pressured her into putting

02:09.127 --> 02:10.463
{\an8}a bottle up her butt.

02:10.547 --> 02:11.631
{\an8}- My little group?

02:11.714 --> 02:14.342
{\an8}You were there, and you didn't
do anything to stop her.

02:14.425 --> 02:15.844
{\an9}- Yeah,
but I wasn't a part of it.

02:15.927 --> 02:17.303
{\an8}- Oh.

02:17.387 --> 02:19.639
{\an8}Is Ethical Ethel
not part of the group anymore?

02:19.722 --> 02:22.725
{\an9}- I'm your friend, but I can't
condone cliquey behavior.

02:22.809 --> 02:24.727
{\an8}- Mary Louise,
do you hear something?

02:24.811 --> 02:27.730
{\an8}It sounds like someone's
talking, but I don't see anyone.

02:27.814 --> 02:28.898
- Are you serious?
- Yeah, Cecelia is talking.

02:28.982 --> 02:32.402
- Cecelia is here?
Oh, where?

02:32.485 --> 02:34.529
I only see people
that are in my "group."

02:34.612 --> 02:35.989
{\an3}- You know what, this is
just like in middle school

02:36.072 --> 02:39.492
{\an3}when I wouldn't help
egg Cindy Hirsch's house

02:39.576 --> 02:42.495
{\an3}because it was mean,
and I was vegan.

02:42.579 --> 02:45.039
- [gasps]
The notebook is floating!

02:45.123 --> 02:47.500
[laughter]

02:47.584 --> 02:49.627
♪ ♪

02:49.711 --> 02:54.340
- Siri, are rectal
foreign objects a frequent cause

02:54.424 --> 02:57.051
of emergency room visits?
[tablet chimes]

02:57.135 --> 02:59.512
<i>- Yes.</i>
both: Hey.

02:59.596 --> 03:01.514
- Turns out
Mary Louise isn't alone.

03:01.598 --> 03:03.558
{\an3}- Dude, since when
do you have an iPad?

03:03.641 --> 03:04.934
{\an3}I thought you said
they were just

03:05.018 --> 03:06.644
{\an3}for stepdads
who were trying to relate.

03:06.728 --> 03:07.979
{\an1}- Yeah, but I got
really into Pinterest.

03:08.062 --> 03:12.525
{\an1}You should see
my Victorian funeral boards.

03:12.609 --> 03:15.153
- How much did this thing cost?
- Nada.

03:15.236 --> 03:17.655
{\an1}I lifted it from
the lost and found.

03:17.739 --> 03:18.740
{\an1}As far as I'm concerned,
after three months,

03:18.823 --> 03:19.949
it's up for grabs.

03:20.033 --> 03:23.453
- It sounds easier
than shoplifting,

03:23.536 --> 03:26.122
{\an3}not that I know anything
about shoplifting.

03:26.205 --> 03:28.124
{\an1}- I just figured
their Lululemon mommies

03:28.207 --> 03:29.792
will buy them new ones.

03:29.876 --> 03:32.629
{\an1}I did almost all my Christmas
shopping in the lost and found.

03:32.712 --> 03:34.339
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

03:34.422 --> 03:36.507
{\an1}Anything you can dream of
is in there,

03:36.591 --> 03:38.760
and about 300 retainers.

03:38.843 --> 03:41.930
- Hey, have you seen any Heelys?
- What are Heelys?

03:42.013 --> 03:44.182
{\an3}- You know, the shoes
with the wheels in them.

03:44.265 --> 03:45.642
You can walk normally,

03:45.725 --> 03:50.229
{\an3}then all of a sudden,
you start rolling forever.

03:50.313 --> 03:53.816
- I know we're all excited
to learn about clouds today,

03:53.900 --> 03:56.945
but last night,
I started to get nostalgic,

03:57.028 --> 04:00.323
and I just thought--yes, Carl?

04:00.406 --> 04:04.994
{\an3}- What does...
n-n-n-n-nostalgic mean?

04:05.078 --> 04:06.621
- It means a bittersweet longing

04:06.704 --> 04:07.997
for people or things
from the past.

04:08.081 --> 04:12.293
Anyway,
I ran into some old friends,

04:12.377 --> 04:15.046
and when I got home,
I went online

04:15.129 --> 04:16.547
and looked up my ex-boyfriend
Jacob's profile.

04:16.630 --> 04:20.551
- But, Ms. Watson, you promised
you wouldn't do that anymore.

04:20.635 --> 04:22.512
- Yeah.
I know I said that, Beth,

04:22.595 --> 04:25.264
but I'm an adult,
and I needed to do this.

04:25.348 --> 04:27.600
- Okay.

04:27.684 --> 04:30.561
- So, who wants
to play a game?

04:30.645 --> 04:32.271
[overlapping chatter]

04:32.355 --> 04:34.232
Great.

04:36.776 --> 04:41.197
This game is called
"Friends or More Than Friends."

04:41.281 --> 04:42.991
I'm gonna show you the photos

04:43.074 --> 04:47.078
that Jacob posted online
of him and this girl,

04:47.161 --> 04:50.331
and I want you to tell me
if they look like friends

04:50.415 --> 04:53.209
or more than friends, okay?

04:56.713 --> 04:59.132
Friends or more than friends?

04:59.215 --> 05:01.134
all: Friends!

05:01.217 --> 05:03.011
- Great.

05:03.094 --> 05:06.973
Friends or more than friends?

05:07.056 --> 05:10.685
all: Friends.

05:10.768 --> 05:13.855
<i>- Friends or more than friends?</i>

05:16.107 --> 05:19.986
It's okay.
You can be honest.

05:22.780 --> 05:25.575
Yes?
- More than friends?

05:25.658 --> 05:27.368
- David,
go to the principal's office!

05:27.452 --> 05:29.454
- But--
- Now!

05:32.373 --> 05:34.208
[door opens and closes]

05:34.292 --> 05:37.420
Okay.

05:37.503 --> 05:41.340
Friends or more than friends?

05:41.424 --> 05:44.052
all: Friends.

05:44.135 --> 05:45.094
- Thank you.

05:45.178 --> 05:46.512
♪ ♪

05:49.724 --> 05:51.559
{\an1}- You shouldn't squint
so much.

05:51.642 --> 05:53.019
You'll start looking
like Keith Richards.

05:53.102 --> 05:54.437
- Yeah, Keith Richards.

05:54.520 --> 05:55.313
- Well, I wouldn't have
to squint if you'd just

05:55.396 --> 05:58.149
{\an3}scoot over
so I could sit in the shade.

05:58.232 --> 06:00.026
{\an1}- Oh, we'd be perfectly willing
to scoot over,

06:00.109 --> 06:00.902
{\an1}but then people might think
you're in the clique.

06:00.985 --> 06:02.278
- Yeah, the clique.

06:02.361 --> 06:05.114
{\an3}- I will never be
in your clique.

06:05.198 --> 06:07.075
Cliques encourage exclusivity,

06:07.158 --> 06:08.785
{\an3}and I want to promote
acceptance.

06:08.868 --> 06:10.161
- Well, how about accepting
that your deodorant crystal

06:10.244 --> 06:13.081
{\an1}can't stand up
to 80 degrees in alpaca?

06:13.164 --> 06:14.040
- Yeah, alpaca.
- Okay, you need to stop that.

06:14.123 --> 06:17.835
- Yeah, stop that.
- Seriously?

06:17.919 --> 06:19.337
- Oh.

06:19.420 --> 06:22.465
- I feel like a sweat lodge
tragedy waiting to happen.

06:22.548 --> 06:24.675
- We have plenty of beverages
to cool you down on this side.

06:24.759 --> 06:27.136
In fact, I'm thirsty.

06:27.220 --> 06:28.763
<i>- Bottle up your butt,</i>
<i>up your butt,</i>

06:28.846 --> 06:31.933
<i>up your butt,</i>
<i>up your butt, up your butt.</i>

06:34.393 --> 06:36.562
{\an3}- [sighs]
All right.

06:36.646 --> 06:38.815
{\an3}I can't take it anymore.
I'm in.

06:38.898 --> 06:42.819
- Yay!
I'm so proud of you.

06:42.902 --> 06:44.862
[laughs]

06:44.946 --> 06:47.657
See, isn't it so fun
over here?

06:47.740 --> 06:49.534
- I'm so happy.

06:49.617 --> 06:50.701
I haven't been this excited

06:50.785 --> 06:52.161
since I convinced
David Weinberger

06:52.245 --> 06:54.997
to accept Jesus Christ
as his Lord and Savior.

06:55.081 --> 06:56.624
♪ ♪

06:56.707 --> 07:01.712
- [sobbing]

07:01.796 --> 07:06.092
{\an1}- Ms. Watson, I wanted to
introduce you to Ginny Groves.

07:08.261 --> 07:11.597
She'll be our substitute
speech therapist for the week.

07:11.681 --> 07:13.349
{\an1}- Hi.
It's nice to meet you.

07:13.432 --> 07:15.351
{\an3}- Oh, wow.
You're here.

07:15.434 --> 07:17.979
- You're the l-l-l-l-lady
from the p-p-p-p--

07:18.062 --> 07:22.692
- Carl, that's enough!

07:22.775 --> 07:24.026
Well, it's great
to have you here, Jenny.

07:24.110 --> 07:27.238
{\an1}- Oh, it's Ginny.
G-I-N-N-Y.

07:27.321 --> 07:28.614
{\an3}- Oh.

07:28.698 --> 07:29.866
{\an3}I would've pronounced
that "Giney."

07:29.949 --> 07:33.786
{\an1}- Well, I will be back a little
later to take Carl from you.

07:33.870 --> 07:34.871
{\an3}- Haven't you
already taken enough?

07:34.954 --> 07:38.124
- What?
- What?

07:38.207 --> 07:40.877
- What?

07:40.960 --> 07:44.505
Ms. Watson, perhaps
you can show Ginny around,

07:44.589 --> 07:46.549
answer any questions Ginny has?

07:46.632 --> 07:47.925
- Of course.

07:48.009 --> 07:50.178
{\an3}And I might even have
some questions for her.

07:50.261 --> 07:55.725
{\an3}[laughs]

07:55.808 --> 07:57.935
Looking forward to it, Giney.
- Ginny.

07:58.019 --> 07:59.645
{\an3}- Uh-huh.

07:59.729 --> 08:00.479
{\an1}- Okay.

08:05.985 --> 08:07.737
- She looks prettier
in person.

08:07.820 --> 08:09.405
- I want you to go
to the corner and think about

08:09.488 --> 08:12.033
what you just said, okay?

08:14.327 --> 08:14.827
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Tear it down ♪</i>

08:14.911 --> 08:17.205
<i>[rock music]</i>

08:17.288 --> 08:19.582
<i>♪ Tear it down ♪</i>

08:19.665 --> 08:21.167
- That's the famous Jacob.

08:21.250 --> 08:22.585
<i>- I can't believe</i>
<i>I have to spend the day</i>

08:22.668 --> 08:25.254
with my ex-boyfriend's
new girlfriend.

08:25.338 --> 08:28.049
- Yeah, she sucks.

08:28.132 --> 08:30.051
What do you think, Cecelia?

08:30.134 --> 08:32.595
{\an1}You're in the group,
aren't you?

08:37.642 --> 08:40.436
- Yeah, she's a tramp.

08:40.519 --> 08:41.604
- Aww, thank you.

08:41.687 --> 08:43.606
- I taught him to do
all that stuff.

08:43.688 --> 08:45.066
<i>When he refused to read</i>
<i>"The Notebook,"</i>

08:45.149 --> 08:46.484
I played the movie
while he slept

08:46.567 --> 08:48.486
so he would subliminally
absorb it.

08:48.569 --> 08:50.071
- Why did you guys
break up again?

08:50.154 --> 08:52.073
- I suggested
we get a puppy, you know,

08:52.156 --> 08:54.492
to warm him up to the idea
of a baby.

08:54.575 --> 08:56.118
<i>But he was so commitment-phobic</i>

08:56.202 --> 08:58.371
that when I brought it up,
he broke up with me over a dog.

08:58.454 --> 09:02.041
- Bastard.
<i>- We were really in love.</i>

09:02.124 --> 09:06.629
I thought we were gonna
get married.

09:06.712 --> 09:08.839
<i>Oh, my God!</i>

09:08.923 --> 09:10.633
<i>That hussy is kissing</i>
<i>my ex-boyfriend</i>

09:10.716 --> 09:12.677
in front of my school!

09:12.760 --> 09:13.803
- Don't worry, girl.

09:13.886 --> 09:15.137
We got your back.
- Yeah.

09:15.221 --> 09:17.557
That bitch better sleep
with one eye open,

09:17.640 --> 09:19.558
or I'm gonna stab her
in the neck!

09:19.642 --> 09:23.604
♪ ♪

09:23.688 --> 09:25.064
- This is the teachers' lounge.

09:25.147 --> 09:27.400
Coffee, doughnuts, you get it.
Moving on.

09:27.483 --> 09:29.402
- Ooh, I love your bracelet.

09:29.485 --> 09:32.530
{\an3}- Thanks.
I made it.

09:32.613 --> 09:33.531
- A fellow crafter?

09:33.614 --> 09:37.410
Do you tumble your own stones?
- Uh, yeah.

09:37.493 --> 09:39.829
{\an3}It's not homemade unless
you tumble your own stones.

09:39.912 --> 09:42.456
{\an1}- That's what I always say.
You know what?

09:42.540 --> 09:43.958
{\an1}I have always wanted
to take that class

09:44.041 --> 09:46.085
{\an1}at the adult learning annex,
but they always fill up.

09:46.168 --> 09:48.421
- Ugh, tell me about it.
- Yes, and when a spot

09:48.504 --> 09:49.964
{\an1}did open up,
it was on a Wednesday

09:50.047 --> 09:51.674
{\an1}when I have
synchronized swimming class.

09:51.757 --> 09:52.842
- Oh, my God.

09:52.925 --> 09:54.427
I also do water ballet.

09:54.510 --> 09:56.012
{\an1}- Okay.
Hold on.

09:56.095 --> 09:57.471
On the count of three,

09:57.555 --> 09:59.390
{\an1}say your favorite
synchronized swimming position.

09:59.473 --> 10:01.183
One, two, three.

10:01.267 --> 10:04.687
both: Dolphin arch!

10:04.770 --> 10:06.188
{\an1}- Everyone always says,
"Flamingo position."

10:06.272 --> 10:07.398
- I know, but it is...

10:07.481 --> 10:09.191
both: A total waste of time!

10:09.275 --> 10:11.610
[both laugh]

10:11.694 --> 10:13.738
{\an3}- Wow!
We have so much in common.

10:13.821 --> 10:16.032
{\an3}You would not believe how many
people don't share my interests!

10:16.115 --> 10:18.075
{\an1}- I know!
We should totally hang out.

10:18.159 --> 10:19.076
- Yes!
- You should come

10:19.160 --> 10:20.077
to a wine tasting with me

10:20.161 --> 10:22.913
and my boyfriend sometime!

10:24.457 --> 10:26.125
- No, I can't.

10:26.208 --> 10:28.377
{\an3}I'm busy.

10:28.461 --> 10:29.879
{\an3}Moving on.

10:29.962 --> 10:33.090
{\an3}- Feldman?

10:33.174 --> 10:35.551
{\an3}Are you trying out
a Harajuku girl lifestyle?

10:35.634 --> 10:36.886
- Sorry, dude.

10:36.969 --> 10:38.721
{\an1}Gotta turn down
these sweet jams.

10:38.804 --> 10:39.639
{\an3}- Is all this stuff
from the lost and found?

10:39.722 --> 10:43.392
{\an1}- Yeah.
But clothes can be problematic.

10:43.476 --> 10:44.727
I fit into this vest,

10:44.810 --> 10:47.355
but I had to cut myself
out of a pair of jeans.

10:47.438 --> 10:49.065
- You're too obvious.

10:49.148 --> 10:51.776
{\an3}You're supposed to keep your eye
on an item for a while,

10:51.859 --> 10:52.985
and then steal it.

10:53.069 --> 10:55.196
{\an1}- Chill out,
McGruff the Crime Dog.

10:55.279 --> 10:58.074
{\an1}I rock this stuff
like I was born wearing it.

10:58.157 --> 10:59.784
- Hey, my sunglasses!

10:59.867 --> 11:01.952
I've been looking for those!

11:02.036 --> 11:04.080
- Well, apparently,
you missed my face

11:04.163 --> 11:06.582
{\an1}because that's where I've been
holding them for you.

11:06.665 --> 11:08.125
{\an3}- You stole them.
I'm telling Principal Pearson.

11:08.209 --> 11:12.046
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.

11:12.129 --> 11:14.548
Here you go.

11:18.636 --> 11:21.889
And here's an iPad
to keep quiet.

11:25.684 --> 11:27.853
{\an1}- What?
One kid noticed.

11:27.937 --> 11:30.523
- Hey, that's my vest!
I'm telling!

11:30.606 --> 11:34.902
Principal Pearson!
Principal Pearson!

11:34.985 --> 11:36.904
{\an1}- Then Tucky surprised me
the other day

11:36.987 --> 11:39.073
with a hot air balloon ride.

11:39.156 --> 11:40.491
{\an3}- "Tucky"?

11:40.574 --> 11:42.660
{\an1}- Oh, I started calling Jacob
that after he surprised me

11:42.743 --> 11:44.662
{\an1}with a trip to Nantucket.
Tucky!

11:44.745 --> 11:46.247
Have you ever been there?

11:46.330 --> 11:46.831
{\an3}- Yeah.

11:46.914 --> 11:48.958
It's my favorite island.

11:49.041 --> 11:50.793
- Oh, he's the best.

11:50.876 --> 11:53.629
- Wow. Sounds like he
doesn't have any flaws

11:53.712 --> 11:57.091
{\an3}like not putting back
your decorative pillows

11:57.174 --> 11:58.717
{\an3}after he makes the bed
or forgetting

11:58.801 --> 12:01.137
{\an3}to use your rose-petal room mist
after using the bathroom.

12:01.220 --> 12:03.305
{\an1}- Oh, he used to do stuff
like that all the time,

12:03.389 --> 12:05.641
but not anymore.

12:05.724 --> 12:09.437
He said he wanted
to change for me.

12:09.520 --> 12:10.938
- Amazing.
- Although,

12:11.021 --> 12:13.482
{\an1}there is one thing about him
that drives me nuts.

12:13.566 --> 12:16.360
{\an3}- Great.
I mean, what is it?

12:16.444 --> 12:17.486
- He's too involved.

12:17.570 --> 12:20.489
{\an1}Sometimes I'm like,
"Okay, just because I'm reading

12:20.573 --> 12:22.825
{\an1}all of Nicholas Sparks' books
doesn't mean you have to."

12:22.908 --> 12:24.994
{\an3}- [laughs]
Right?

12:25.077 --> 12:28.539
{\an1}- Right.

12:28.622 --> 12:30.374
{\an3}- [grunts]

12:30.458 --> 12:33.544
{\an3}This potholder
is taking forever.

12:33.627 --> 12:37.298
- Oh, I just finished mine.

12:37.381 --> 12:39.091
The T is for "Tucky."

12:44.054 --> 12:46.557
- You know what you
and Tucky should do?

12:46.640 --> 12:48.017
{\an1}- What?

12:48.100 --> 12:51.687
- You should adopt a dog.

12:51.770 --> 12:53.522
{\an1}- Aww.

12:53.606 --> 12:55.733
[laughter]

12:55.816 --> 12:57.109
- This will teach her to date

12:57.193 --> 12:58.861
one of our friends'
ex-boyfriends!

12:58.944 --> 13:00.321
[laughter]

13:00.404 --> 13:01.363
- You spelled the name wrong.

13:01.447 --> 13:02.823
It's Ginny with a G.

13:02.907 --> 13:04.700
- I know.
I'm being mean.

13:04.783 --> 13:07.203
[laughter]

13:07.286 --> 13:09.872
{\an3}- I just took a dump
in her desk.

13:09.955 --> 13:11.874
- Oh, my God.

13:11.957 --> 13:13.334
It's not even her desk.

13:13.417 --> 13:15.711
- She's a sub.
- This clique rules!

13:15.794 --> 13:18.047
I don't know why I didn't
do this in middle school.

13:18.130 --> 13:19.548
{\an3}[gasps]
Oh, my God!

13:19.632 --> 13:21.258
Have you guys seen
the movie "Carrie"?

13:21.342 --> 13:24.303
{\an3}I have pig's blood in my trunk
from my last protest.

13:24.386 --> 13:26.639
I'll be right back!

13:26.722 --> 13:29.225
