13:34.563 --> 13:36.357
<i>♪ Tear it down ♪</i>

13:36.440 --> 13:38.400
{\an1}- [sobbing]
Oh, there you are.

13:38.484 --> 13:39.818
I've been looking
all over for you.

13:39.902 --> 13:41.529
- What's wrong?

13:41.612 --> 13:44.156
{\an3}Did you get shut out
of the herbal soap making class?

13:44.240 --> 13:47.201
{\an1}- No.
Jacob and I broke up.

13:47.284 --> 13:50.496
I just feel sick.

13:50.579 --> 13:53.457
{\an1}[sobbing]

13:53.541 --> 13:54.625
- What happened?

13:54.708 --> 13:57.461
{\an1}- Last night, we got home
from a couple's cooking class.

13:57.545 --> 13:59.255
- You guys go to cooking class?
- Yeah.

13:59.338 --> 14:02.925
{\an1}And everything was going fine
until I decided to bring up

14:03.008 --> 14:04.593
{\an1}getting a dog
like you suggested.

14:04.677 --> 14:06.637
- Uh-huh?
- And he totally freaked out,

14:06.720 --> 14:09.306
{\an1}and he said
that that was exactly

14:09.390 --> 14:11.308
what happened with his ex.

14:11.392 --> 14:13.435
{\an1}[sobbing]

14:13.519 --> 14:15.145
{\an3}- Did he say anything
else about her?

14:15.229 --> 14:18.941
{\an1}- What?
No.

14:19.024 --> 14:21.819
{\an1}And then, before I knew it,
he was just--

14:21.902 --> 14:24.154
he said it was over!

14:24.238 --> 14:26.156
{\an1}And then, this morning,
I get here,

14:26.240 --> 14:28.784
{\an1}and some students
had vandalized my office.

14:28.867 --> 14:31.537
- That's terrible.
- Someone actually defecated

14:31.620 --> 14:33.581
in my desk drawer.
- Oh, my God.

14:33.664 --> 14:34.498
{\an1}- And I'm pretty sure
they were vegan

14:34.582 --> 14:38.836
'cause the smell was awful.

14:38.919 --> 14:40.921
- Oh, my God.

14:41.005 --> 14:44.341
- And I just--ugh!

14:44.425 --> 14:48.345
{\an1}I've never had my heart broken
like this before.

14:48.429 --> 14:50.598
I thought he was the one.

14:50.681 --> 14:52.474
{\an3}- I know.

14:52.558 --> 14:56.145
It's the worst feeling.

14:57.646 --> 15:01.317
{\an1}- I've got to go
disinfect my desk.

15:01.400 --> 15:03.402
But maybe we can talk later?

15:03.485 --> 15:05.070
{\an3}- Sure.

15:05.154 --> 15:07.364
{\an1}- Okay.

15:07.448 --> 15:11.035
You're an angel.

15:14.079 --> 15:16.832
- I'm a monster.

15:16.915 --> 15:19.376
{\an3}- Crap!
Did I miss her?

15:20.336 --> 15:22.171
- No running!

15:22.254 --> 15:26.008
{\an1}- Dude, I'm sorry I derailed
your lost and found gravy train.

15:26.091 --> 15:29.261
{\an3}- It's okay.
I knew it was too good to last.

15:29.345 --> 15:30.721
- You put all your stuff back?

15:30.804 --> 15:32.890
{\an3}- Yeah.
My husband's gonna be pissed

15:32.973 --> 15:33.849
{\an3}when he realizes
half our Xbox games

15:33.932 --> 15:37.144
{\an3}and our stash
of ADD meds are gone.

15:37.227 --> 15:39.188
- Hmm.
- Did you return everything?

15:39.271 --> 15:41.023
- Yeah.
- Really?

15:41.106 --> 15:42.691
- Mm-hmm.
- Feldman.

15:42.775 --> 15:44.318
- Smell you later.

15:44.401 --> 15:47.363
<i>[uplifting music]</i>

15:47.446 --> 15:50.532
♪ ♪

15:50.616 --> 15:52.660
{\an3}- You bounce back
surprisingly quickly

15:52.743 --> 15:54.203
{\an3}after putting a bottle
up your butt.

15:54.286 --> 15:55.871
- You know,
the human body's pretty amazing,

15:55.954 --> 15:57.289
the way it heals itself.

15:57.373 --> 15:58.415
<i>- Oh, my God, you guys!</i>

15:58.499 --> 15:59.958
Guess what! Hey!

16:00.042 --> 16:01.877
{\an3}What did I tell you,
you bald freak?

16:01.960 --> 16:02.628
You don't sit at our table!

16:02.711 --> 16:05.756
<i>Get the hell out of here!</i>

16:08.133 --> 16:10.135
{\an3}[laughs]

16:10.219 --> 16:12.930
{\an1}- What is wrong with you?
That is Mr. Spinnoli.

16:13.013 --> 16:14.932
- He teaches special ed.

16:15.015 --> 16:16.183
- So?
- Okay.

16:16.266 --> 16:17.351
I can't take it anymore.

16:17.434 --> 16:18.936
I am dissolving this clique.
- What?

16:19.019 --> 16:20.104
- You are out of control.

16:20.187 --> 16:22.231
This morning's desk incident?

16:22.314 --> 16:23.607
Who can poop on cue?

16:23.691 --> 16:24.566
{\an3}- I doubled up
on my mung beans.

16:24.650 --> 16:27.236
- This clique used to be fun,

16:27.319 --> 16:29.738
but now it's kind of scary.
- Yeah.

16:29.822 --> 16:32.157
{\an1}I dated a Latin King once,
and it was not this bad.

16:32.241 --> 16:33.742
- So we're done?
- Yeah.

16:33.826 --> 16:35.661
We are done.

16:35.744 --> 16:37.162
{\an3}- Good.

16:37.246 --> 16:38.664
I'm glad I made my point.

16:38.747 --> 16:43.377
- What point?

16:43.460 --> 16:45.754
{\an3}- I decided the best way
to show you

16:45.838 --> 16:48.006
how awful cliques were
was to infiltrate yours

16:48.090 --> 16:49.466
and mimic your behavior...

16:49.550 --> 16:53.137
to affect social change.

16:53.220 --> 16:56.557
{\an1}- Right.
You took a dump for change.

16:57.850 --> 17:00.269
{\an1}- I just can't believe
it's over.

17:00.352 --> 17:01.729
- Don't beat yourself up.

17:01.812 --> 17:04.106
{\an3}It's perfectly reasonable
to want a dog.

17:04.189 --> 17:05.941
{\an1}- You're absolutely right,
Caroline.

17:06.023 --> 17:07.984
{\an1}You know what?
I am so glad we met.

17:08.068 --> 17:10.988
You...you have been
such a great friend.

17:14.116 --> 17:18.537
{\an3}- Actually, that's not true.
Listen--

17:18.619 --> 17:19.788
- Excuse me.
Where's the teachers' lounge?

17:19.872 --> 17:24.001
Oh, thank you.
Thank you.

17:24.084 --> 17:25.335
- Oh, my pen!
- What?

17:25.419 --> 17:29.256
{\an1}- Ginny.

17:29.339 --> 17:30.299
I need to talk to you.

17:30.382 --> 17:32.009
- Jacob,
what are you doing here?

17:32.092 --> 17:33.719
- I freaked out yesterday.

17:33.802 --> 17:34.928
I-I blew it.

17:35.012 --> 17:36.388
- Did you get me a puppy?

17:36.472 --> 17:41.977
- No, I got <i> us</i> a puppy.

17:42.060 --> 17:45.481
{\an1}And that's not all.
Here.

17:45.564 --> 17:49.318
{\an1}I've never met another woman
like you.

17:49.401 --> 17:50.486
{\an1}No one has ever measured
up to you.

17:50.569 --> 17:52.946
No one ever will.

17:53.030 --> 17:57.326
{\an1}Virginia Anne Groves...
will you marry me?

17:57.409 --> 18:01.163
- Tucky!

18:01.246 --> 18:04.333
Yes!
Yes!

18:04.416 --> 18:05.417
- Are you kidding me?

18:05.501 --> 18:09.213
{\an3}<i>Did you seriously just propose</i>
<i>at my school?</i>

18:09.296 --> 18:11.924
I did everything for you.

18:12.007 --> 18:15.177
Eat [bleep]! Eat [bleep]!
Eat [bleep]! Eat [bleep]!

18:15.260 --> 18:16.345
Eat [bleep]!

18:16.428 --> 18:18.180
You, sir, can eat [bleep]!

18:18.263 --> 18:19.348
Eat [bleep]!
Eat [bleep]!

18:19.431 --> 18:20.516
Eat all of the [bleep]!

18:20.599 --> 18:21.183
Just eat it!

18:21.266 --> 18:22.851
<i>You're a</i> [bleep] <i> eater!</i>

18:22.935 --> 18:24.478
Eat [bleep]! Eat [bleep]!

18:24.561 --> 18:26.980
{\an3}Eat it!
Eat [bleep]!

18:31.527 --> 18:33.237
{\an3}Ginny...

18:33.320 --> 18:36.740
{\an3}I wish you all the happiness
in the world.

18:36.824 --> 18:42.579
This is a really great dog.

18:42.663 --> 18:44.873
Jacob, you can eat [bleep].

18:44.957 --> 18:46.917
{\an1}- Yeah.

18:50.504 --> 18:52.548
